Newcastle stand-in skipper Moussa Sissoko is facing disciplinary action after he was sent off following a reckless challenge on Liverpool midfielder Lucas Leiva during Monday's 2-0 defeat at Anfield.

The France international was given a second yellow card for the offence, but head coach John Carver feels it should have been a straight red.

'The club will deal with that situation,' he said when asked if Sissoko - who is now banned for two matches - would be punished.

