'He knows he was wrong. He was fortunate not to get a straight red and he agreed with me.

'He apologised afterwards to Lucas, which was important.

'But you think captains would lead by example. We have to improve our discipline. I will be looking at that.'

Meanwhile, Carver says Newcastle cannot rely on the shortcomings of others to preserve their Premier League status.

The Magpies are the division's most out-of-form side having lost five on the spin, scoring just one goal along the way.

